Subject: [announce] Vicare/libESMTP revision 0.4d1

			    Vicare/libESMTP
			    ===============


This package  is a  distribution of  C and  Scheme libraries  for Vicare
Scheme, an R6RS compliant Scheme implementation  in the form of a native
compiler for x86 architectures, officially supporting GNU+Linux systems;
it provides bindings for the libESMTP C language library.

  This package makes use of the GNU Autotools.

  The latest version of this package can be downloaded from:

      <https://bitbucket.org/marcomaggi/vicare-libesmtp/downloads>

the home page of the Vicare project is at:

	       <http://marcomaggi.github.io/vicare.html>

development takes place at:

	    <http://github.com/marcomaggi/vicare-libesmtp/>

and as backup at:

	  <https://bitbucket.org/marcomaggi/vicare-libesmtp/>

  The last  time the author  bothered to  update this paragraph,  he had
tested libESMTP version 1.0.7rc1; the libESMTP library is available at:

	      <http://www.stafford.uklinux.net/libesmtp/>


Notes for revision 0.4d1
------------------------

* Ensure support for Vicare Scheme 0.4d1.


Notes for revision 0.4d0
------------------------

* Started support for Vicare Scheme 0.4.


Notes for revision 0.2d0
------------------------

* Updated to and dependent on Vicare Scheme 0.3.


Notes for revision 0.1d0
------------------------

* Development release.  Comments and testing are welcome.

* Neither AUTH nor SSL supported so far.  Coming in the next release.


